Creating a template with markup such as:
{metadata-list}
|Name|@Name@|
{metadata-list}

Results in templates that give completely blank markup when the insert variables button is pressed

Take this JQL query for example:

{code}
"RT3 Ticket Number" = 1792
{code}

The permalink to the query would be:

{code}
http://jira/secure/IssueNavigator!executeAdvanced.jspa?runQuery=true&clear=true&jqlQuery=%22RT3+Ticket+Number%22+%3D+1792
{code}

If this is added as a Confluence shortcut URL e.g. \[1792@rt3]

{code}
http://jira/secure/IssueNavigator!executeAdvanced.jspa?runQuery=true&clear=true&jqlQuery=%22RT3+Ticket+Number%22+%3D
{code}

JIRA will not be able to parse the escaped JQL query. Same goes to this "tweaked" URL:

{code}
http://jira/secure/IssueNavigator!executeAdvanced.jspa?runQuery=true&clear=true&jqlQuery="RT3 Ticket Number" = %s
{code}

The url that gets generated looks like:

{code}
http://anf.ucsd.edu/jira/secure/IssueNavigator!executeAdvanced.jspa?runQuery=true&clear=true&jqlQuery%3d%22RT3+Ticket+Number%22+%3D+1792
{code}

